text: I guess any object that functions as a weight has the potential of giving birth unto a strength culture in itself

Early kettlebells were just balance weights that were used to weigh grain, flour, etc. on the weight scales in windmills or exchanges so farmers started lifting them and competing against each other while being bored waiting for milling to finish, others to be done, etc.
